HEADWORD: Hemstitch
<hw>Hem"stitch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hemstitched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Hemstitching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[<ets>Hem</ets> +
<ets>stitch</ets>.]</ety> <def>To ornament at the head of a broad hem by
drawing out a few parallel threads, and fastening the cross threads in
successive small clusters; <as>as, to <ex>hemstitch</ex> a
handkerchief</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemstitched</ent>⟦br⟧
